Class NewRelationship

  • java.lang.Object
    • subrelationshipsfinder.NewRelationship

  • public class NewRelationship
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents the path the user has provided, which we call here the new relationship. Contains the path, the class domain and range.

      • createPathsTable

        public java.util.Hashtable<java.lang.Integer,java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String[]>> createPathsTable(MRepositoryManager mrmb)
        This category will take the path provided by the user and split it in the different paths it can be split (NOT the ORs in predicates). The different paths will be stored in a hashtable. The original path must be set in the object's variable pathString using the respective setter method.

        Returns:
